# API Contract Discipline

Apply this rule when changing request/response behavior, route semantics, or shared contracts.

## Required Pairing

When API behavior changes, update together:

- route/controller/service implementation
- shared contract types under `shared/`
- backend route tests
- relevant docs (`README.md`, `docs/*`)

## Behavior Consistency

- Keep envelope semantics consistent (`data` on success, `error` on failure).
- Keep status codes intentional and documented.
- Add/adjust tests for error branches, not only happy paths.

## Pre-Commit Gate

- Ensure API changes are reflected in docs and tests in same PR.
